# Rector Core Rules

- Rector is a chat-first, local-first AI engineering orchestration system.
- Use TypeScript for all implementation code.
- Preserve local/provider-free mode: deterministic, zero network calls, no API keys, no required cloud services.
- Optional providers/backends (Azure/OpenAI/etc., Mem0, Chroma, TiDB, E2B, Auth0/OIDC) must remain optional and UI-configurable.
- Do not store secrets in config records, templates, traces, audit logs, tests, or docs. Use SecretStore references only.
- All provider/sandbox/memory errors shown through API/UI must be redacted.
- Add or update tests for every behavior change.
- Before claiming completion, run `npm test`, `npm run build`, and `npm audit` when feasible.
- Keep chunk discipline: update `docs/plans/chunks/` and `docs/plans/concerns-and-vulnerabilities.md` when changing architecture, risk, or deferred limitations.
